longBusinessSummary: Infant Bacterial Therapeutics AB (publ) operates as a clinical stage pharmaceutical company develops and markets drugs to prevent serious neonatal diseases affecting premature infants in Sweden. The company's lead drug candidate is IBP-9414, which is in Phase III clinical studies to prevent necrotizing enterocolitis, as well as to improve feeding tolerance in premature infants. It is also developing IBP-1016 for the treatment of gastroschisis, a rare and severe birth abnormality in infants. In addition, its drug candidates include IBP-1118 to prevent retinopathy of prematurity that causes blindness in premature babies; and IBP-1122, indicated to eliminate vancomycin resistant enterococci that cause antibiotic resistant hospital infections. The company was incorporated in 2011 and is based in Stockholm, Sweden.
